10:
Jeez... Done already? That crazy
firepower of yours never ceases to
amaze.
15:
Nyahaha, well, did you see all those
enemies? Of course I had to pull out
the big guns.
20:
But you attacked without reporting
in first... Is that okay?
23:
That's because the guys back at the
office have been acting weird
lately... If I'm not careful, they might
grab weapons and try fighting
themselves!
26:
And then before I know it, someone
gets hurt... Filing a report after an
attack is more work, but all they'll do
is scold me, so it's fine.
29: Hey there! This is Tink, how's it—
36:
H-hold on. What do you mean, he's
hurt?!
46: Do you think the old man's okay?
50:
...Doesn't matter how much we
worry, all we can do is wait. It's not
like he died, anyway.
60:
He'll be fine. He's just sleeping. It
doesn't seem to be serious.
63:
You two know what happened, don't
you? Who injured him like that?
65:
...It was foul play. He was performing
a private investigation and
discovered an enemy in our midst.
69:
A private investigation?! And you
two knew? Since when?!
72: Why was I left in the dark about this?
75:
This is just the result of the
higher-ups' endless disputes.
Another drop in the bucket.
76:
There wasn't a point in involving you
if you weren't already aware. He
didn't want you getting your hands
dirty.
79:
What kinda crap is that? Now you're
making me mad.
81:
I thought we were supposed to be a
team!
85: I will NOT stand for this!
88:
A team, huh? She did say something
like that in the beginning, didn't she?
94: Let's see... You're Chief Tink, correct?
95:
What an adorable boss we have.
Are you sure it's okay that I won't be
much use in a fight?
98:
Nyahaha, of course it is! Just leave
all the fighting to yours truly!
103:
You bet! Starting today, we're a
team, and I have absolute faith in us!
111:
Rivaling factions... 3MM Security
affiliates... Noxel Group bylaws...
115:
Ohhh, I don't understand a word of
this mumbo jumbo!
119:
Y-you scared me for a second
there... Didn't expect to see anyone
here so late.
123:
Nyahaha, sorry about that. Did you
forget something here?
126:
Yeah... What about you? Why are
you here?
129:
Ah, well... I guess you could call it
research, but it feels more like
studying...
132:
I'm looking into what the old man
was doing.
135:
That's... incredible. You're already
taking action.
138: No... It's not incredible at all...
140:
I should have been doing this from
the beginning. But I put it off, and
now I don't understand a word of
this.
144:
That's not like me at all! I usually
have my crap together.
147: Who knew I was this stupid?!
151:
...I guess I've always been afraid that
something like this would happen.
That I'd fail.
155:
Well, that doesn't look like it's
stopping you from doing something
about it.
160:
Nyahaha, true, true. And I'm just
getting started.
162:
The most important part of falling
down is getting back up, after all.
165:
That being said, I haven't even
gotten my bearings after falling yet.
168:
Come to think of it, didn't you say
something about being a team
earlier?
183:
Okay, everybody! Put on your
thinking caps and get those brains
in motion!
187:
Yeah, we're gonna need more of an
explanation than that.
190:
Awww, I thought that'd be enough.
All right, if you insist.
193:
I can't do this on my own. So
please... help me.
196:
...Hmph. I was wondering when you
were going to ask. Better late than
never, I suppose.
203: What about you two? Are you in?
207:
You bet. We couldn't just up and
leave now.
215:
Oho, kids these days.... Always full of
surprises.
217:
Well, looks like it's time for these old
bones to get to work.
